At least 32 people have died, and 19 remain missing following Friday's explosion at the Hotel Saratoga in Havana, the provincial head of the Front for Restoring Family Contacts of the Red Cross, Gloria Bonnin told Cuba's state-run Prensa Latina News Agency on Saturday. (Cover: Emergency crews work at the site of an explosion that destroyed the five-star Hotel Saratoga in Old Havana, Cuba, May 6, 2022. /CFP)